Asian Center for Theological Studies and Mission ( or ACTS ) is an interdenominational evangelical Christian school in South Korea . It has two primary campuses : the smaller original location in Seoul , a larger new campus in Yangpyeong County , west of Seoul in central Gyeonggi province . It hosts undergraduate and graduate programs on a number of campuses . The school traces its roots to an evangelical conference in Singapore in 1968 . The campus was opened in Seoul 's Seodaemun - gu on May 1 , 1974 , with six students . At that time it existed only as the Asia Center for Theological Studies and Mission ; it received permission to form an educational corporation in 1981 , at which time the formal entity of Asia United Theological College was established . Shortly thereafter the Yangpyeong campus was acquired . The college became a university in 1993 . 